<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-11-10T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-11-10T03:00:00-05:00" n="362" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d362">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">693.003/796: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-11-10T16:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">November 10,
                                        1927—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received November 10—11:15
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>984. 1. On October 17, the Senior Minister informed the Minister of
                            Foreign Affairs that the diplomatic body agreed to the continuation in
                            Peking of the work of the Tariff Valuation Revision Commission.</p>
                        <p>2. The Minister of Foreign Affairs has now notified this Legation the
                            next Commission will convene here on December 1st.</p>
                        <p>3. Commercial attaché suggests that the Department request the Treasury
                            to instruct Nicholson<note n="56" xml:id="d362fn56">Martin R. Nicholson,
                                Treasury representative at Shanghai.</note> to proceed to Peking for
                            this purpose. I concur.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>